    "nuumi_faq": {
      "type": "nuumi-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Which product should I start with?",
            "answer": "<p>Start with whatever's making your dog's life hardest right now. Anxiety or reactivity — start with CalmiCollar. Digestion, low energy, gut problems — start with EnerCanis.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I use more than one product at the same time?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes — and most owners end up doing exactly that. CalmiCollar handles the stress running underneath while the training tools work on the specific behaviors you're seeing day to day. EnerCanis can run alongside either of them since it's working on a completely different system. They're designed to cover different jobs, so there's no conflict.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How quickly will I see results?",
            "answer": "<p>Depends on the product. CalmiCollar typically shows changes within the first few days. EnerCanis works on gut health, so most owners notice a shift in energy and digestion within 2-3 weeks. Training tools depend on consistency — but owners who follow the methods usually see progress in the first week.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What if it doesn't work for my dog?",
            "answer": "<p>Every Nuumipet product comes with a money-back guarantee. If you don't see results, reach out and we'll take care of it. We'd rather you try it knowing the risk is on us than wonder whether it could have helped.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Are the ingredients safe for all breeds and ages?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. Every formula uses natural ingredients that are safe across breeds and life stages. But if your dog has a specific medical condition or is on medication, it’s always recommended to check with your vet first.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
